mem_profile <- profmem({
    time_taken <- system.time({
        # Extract gene names
        seurat_subset$mt <- grepl("^MT-", seurat_subset@misc$gene_metadata$Gene)
        seurat_subset$ribo <- grepl("^(RPS|RPL)", seurat_subset@misc$gene_metadata$Gene)
        seurat_subset$hb <- grepl("^HB[^P]", seurat_subset@misc$gene_metadata$Gene)

        # Calculate the percentage of mitochondrial genes
        seurat_subset <- PercentageFeatureSet(seurat_subset, pattern = "^MT-", col.name = "percent.mt")
        # Calculate the percentage of ribosomal genes
        seurat_subset <- PercentageFeatureSet(seurat_subset, pattern = "^(RPS|RPL)", col.name = "percent.ribo")
        # Calculate the percentage of hemoglobin genes
        seurat_subset <- PercentageFeatureSet(seurat_subset, pattern = "^HB[^P]", col.name = "percent.hb")


        # Calculate the number of cells with non-zero counts for each gene
        n_cells <- Matrix::rowSums(GetAssayData(seurat_subset, assay = "RNA", layer = "counts") > 0)
        n_cells_metadata <- data.frame(n_cells = n_cells, row.names = rownames(seurat_subset))
        seurat_subset[["RNA"]] <- AddMetaData(seurat_subset[["RNA"]], metadata = n_cells_metadata)
  })
})

seurat_subset <- subset(seurat_subset, nFeature_RNA >= 300) # Filter cells with min_genes=100
seurat_subset <- subset(seurat_subset, nFeature_RNA <= 6000) # Filter cells with min_genes=100
seurat_subset <- subset(seurat_subset, nCount_RNA <= 40000) # Filter on total_counts <= 40000
seurat_subset <- subset(seurat_subset, percent.mt <= 20) # Filter on pct_counts_mt <= 20

# Filter on sc.pp.filter_genes(adata_subset, min_cells=3)
genes_to_keep <- rownames(seurat_subset)[seurat_subset[["RNA"]]@meta.data$n_cells >= 3]

In [12]:
result <- bench::mark(
  {
    # Split by batch
    batch_list <- SplitObject(seurat_subset, split.by = "donor_id")

    # Find HVGs for each batch
    hvgs_list <- lapply(batch_list, function(obj) {
        obj <- FindVariableFeatures(obj, selection.method = "dispersion", nfeatures = 2000)
        VariableFeatures(obj)
    })

    # Combine HVGs across batches (not sorted)
    combined_hvgs <- unique(unlist(hvgs_list))
  },
  iterations = 1
)

cat("Wall time:", result$total_time, "\n")

Leiden¶

  • Running FindClusters() Twice: Each call to FindClusters() re-applies the Leiden clustering process, providing a rough approximation of n_iterations=2 in scanpy.
  • No n_iterations Parameter: Seurat does not expose this parameter, so multiple calls are the closest approximation.

seurat_object@misc$counts_gs <- raw_counts

rownames(normalized_data) <- mapped_symbols
seurat_object@misc$data_gs <- normalized_data

scaled_data <- GetAssayData(seurat_object, assay = "RNA", slot = "scale.data")
